.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-27 text note references. This NIP standardizes inline
references to other events and profiles within event content using
\&\f(CW\*(C`nostr:\*(C'\fR URIs (NIP\-21) containing NIP\-19 bech32\-encoded entities.
.PP
When creating events, use "mention_pubkey", "mention_event", and
"mention_addr" to produce properly formatted \f(CW\*(C`nostr:\*(C'\fR URIs to embed
in content.
.PP
When displaying events, use "extract_mentions" to find all references
in content, and "replace_mentions" to substitute them with display
text such as profile names or event previews.
.PP
Including \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`q\*(C'\fR tags for mentioned entities is optional
per NIP\-27. Clients should add tags when they want the mentioned profile
to be notified or the referenced event to recognize the mention as a
reply.
.SH FUNCTIONS
.IX Header "FUNCTIONS"
All functions are exportable. None are exported by default.
.SS extract_mentions
.IX Subsection "extract_mentions"
.Vb 1
\&    my @mentions = extract_mentions($content);
.Ve
.PP
Finds all \f(CW\*(C`nostr:\*(C'\fR URIs in the given content string. Returns a list of
hashrefs, one per mention, in order of appearance. Each hashref contains:
.ie n .IP """type"" \- entity type: ""npub"", ""note"", ""nprofile"", ""nevent"", or ""naddr""" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWtype\fR \- entity type: \f(CWnpub\fR, \f(CWnote\fR, \f(CWnprofile\fR, \f(CWnevent\fR, or \f(CWnaddr\fR" 4
.IX Item "type - entity type: npub, note, nprofile, nevent, or naddr"
.PD 0
.ie n .IP """data"" \- decoded data: hex string for bare types (""npub"", ""note""), hashref for TLV types (""nprofile"", ""nevent"", ""naddr"")" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWdata\fR \- decoded data: hex string for bare types (\f(CWnpub\fR, \f(CWnote\fR), hashref for TLV types (\f(CWnprofile\fR, \f(CWnevent\fR, \f(CWnaddr\fR)" 4
.IX Item "data - decoded data: hex string for bare types (npub, note), hashref for TLV types (nprofile, nevent, naddr)"
.ie n .IP """uri"" \- the full ""nostr:..."" string as it appeared in content" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWuri\fR \- the full \f(CWnostr:...\fR string as it appeared in content" 4
.IX Item "uri - the full nostr:... string as it appeared in content"
.ie n .IP """start"" \- byte offset of the start of the URI in content" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWstart\fR \- byte offset of the start of the URI in content" 4
.IX Item "start - byte offset of the start of the URI in content"
.ie n .IP """end"" \- byte offset of the end of the URI in content" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWend\fR \- byte offset of the end of the URI in content" 4
.IX Item "end - byte offset of the end of the URI in content"
.PD
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`nsec\*(C'\fR URIs are silently skipped (they must not appear in \f(CW\*(C`nostr:\*(C'\fR URIs
per NIP\-21). Invalid bech32 strings are silently skipped.
.PP
.Vb 9
\&    use Net::Nostr::Bech32 qw(encode_npub);
\&    my $npub = encode_npub(\*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32);
\&    my $content = "hello nostr:$npub world";
\&    my @m = extract_mentions($content);
\&    say $m[0]{type};   # \*(Aqnpub\*(Aq
\&    say $m[0]{start};  # 6
\&    say substr($content, $m[0]{start}, $m[0]{end} \- $m[0]{start});
\&    # nostr:npub1...
\&    say $m[0]{data};   # \*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32
.Ve
.SS replace_mentions
.IX Subsection "replace_mentions"
.Vb 1
\&    my $display = replace_mentions($content, \e&callback);
.Ve
.PP
Replaces each \f(CW\*(C`nostr:\*(C'\fR mention in content with the return value of the
callback. The callback receives a mention hashref (same structure as
"extract_mentions") and should return a replacement string.
.PP
.Vb 11
\&    use Net::Nostr::Bech32 qw(encode_npub encode_note);
\&    my $npub = encode_npub(\*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32);
\&    my $note = encode_note(\*(Aqbb\*(Aq x 32);
\&    my $content = "by nostr:$npub see nostr:$note";
\&    my $display = replace_mentions($content, sub {
\&        my ($m) = @_;
\&        return \*(Aq@\*(Aq . substr($m\->{data}, 0, 8) . \*(Aq...\*(Aq if $m\->{type} eq \*(Aqnpub\*(Aq;
\&        return \*(Aq[event]\*(Aq if $m\->{type} eq \*(Aqnote\*(Aq || $m\->{type} eq \*(Aqnevent\*(Aq;
\&        return $m\->{uri};
\&    });
\&    # \*(Aqby @aaaaaaaa... see [event]\*(Aq
.Ve
.SS mention_pubkey
.IX Subsection "mention_pubkey"
.Vb 2
\&    my $uri = mention_pubkey($hex_pubkey);
\&    my $uri = mention_pubkey($hex_pubkey, relays => [\*(Aqwss://relay.com\*(Aq]);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a \f(CW\*(C`nostr:\*(C'\fR URI for a public key. Returns \f(CW\*(C`nostr:npub1...\*(C'\fR when
no options are given, or \f(CW\*(C`nostr:nprofile1...\*(C'\fR when relay hints are provided.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    my $pk = \*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32;
\&    my $content = "hello " . mention_pubkey($pk) . " how are you?";
\&    # \*(Aqhello nostr:npub1... how are you?\*(Aq
.Ve
.SS mention_event
.IX Subsection "mention_event"
.Vb 2
\&    my $uri = mention_event($hex_event_id);
\&    my $uri = mention_event($hex_event_id, relays => \e@r, author => $pk, kind => $k);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a \f(CW\*(C`nostr:\*(C'\fR URI for an event. Returns \f(CW\*(C`nostr:note1...\*(C'\fR when no
options are given, or \f(CW\*(C`nostr:nevent1...\*(C'\fR when any of \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`author\*(C'\fR,
or \f(CW\*(C`kind\*(C'\fR are provided.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $pk = \*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32;
\&    my $id = \*(Aqbb\*(Aq x 32;
\&    my $content = "see " . mention_event($id, author => $pk, kind => 1);
\&    # \*(Aqsee nostr:nevent1...\*(Aq
.Ve
.SS mention_addr
.IX Subsection "mention_addr"
.Vb 6
\&    my $uri = mention_addr(
\&        identifier => $d_tag,
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        kind       => $kind,
\&        relays     => \e@relays,   # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a \f(CW\*(C`nostr:naddr1...\*(C'\fR URI for an addressable event. \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`kind\*(C'\fR are required. \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR is optional.
.PP
.Vb 5
\&    my $pk = \*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32;
\&    my $content = "read " . mention_addr(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqmy\-article\*(Aq, pubkey => $pk, kind => 30023,
\&    );
\&    # \*(Aqread nostr:naddr1...\*(Aq
.Ve
